ooting f a British ambassador but talks softly to Italy over the hooting up of British shipping Russia sends an angry ote to Italy over sinking of tankers supplying the Spanish overnment but temporizes with Japan over the sinking of lg_yiet gun bo_gts on the Amur Such is medern diplomacy These notesendings are all done for strategic reasonsfor their ef fect upon third parties They are attempts to invole outside elements in rescue The British note to Japan if intended to impress Japan would not have emphasized the shooting of noncombatan in which Britain herself has l\ufb02d frequently and recently It would have stressed in stead the insult to imperial majesty to which the Emperorworshiping Japanese must have responded But the British foreign"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-06-05T16:47:12.034Z", "group": ["ndnp/txdn", "university-of-north-texas-denton-tx-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86089568/1937-09-15/ed-1/?sp=3", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:txdn:batch_txdn_crane_ver01:data:sn86089568:00517176564:1937091501:0814/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=316&w=240", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:txdn:batch_txdn_crane_ver01:data:sn86089568:00517176564:1937091501:0814/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=633&w=480", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_crane_ver01/data/sn86089568/00517176564/1937091501/0814.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 3, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "webb", "laredo", "texas"], "location_city": ["laredo"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["webb"], "location_state": ["texas"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number": ["5", "0000000003", "0", "sn86089568", "1", "4", "7", "6"], "number_edition": ["1"], "number_lccn": ["sn86089568"], "number_page": [